# Deploy to Google Drive After Changes

**One-way flow only:** Changes flow Main Project (MARS ADO MCP) → Deployment (Center of Excellence (CoE)/MCP Servers). Never the reverse.

**REQUIRED:** After making any changes to MCP commands, tools, prompts, bootstrap, or enhancements, you MUST deploy the updated files to the Google Drive folder.

## Keep Documentation Up to Date

**REQUIRED:** Every code change must update the relevant documentation:

- **docs/implementation.md** — MCP tools inventory, conventions, field mapping, API reference
- **docs/setup-guide.md** — Command tables, setup steps
- **docs/testing-guide.md** — Tool quick reference, slash commands, troubleshooting
- **docs/tc-style-guide-and-consistency-strategy.md** — TC style and consistency rules

## Deploy Command

```bash
npm run deploy
```

This builds the distribution and copies it to the configured Google Drive folder (Center of Excellence (CoE)/MCP Servers).

## When to Deploy

- After adding or modifying MCP tools
- After changing the installer or bootstrap
- After updating setup-guide.md or conventions.config.json
- After any enhancement that affects the user-facing MCP

## Setup

Create `.deploy-path` (or set `GDRIVE_DEPLOY_PATH` env var) with the target folder path. See `.deploy-path.example`.
